cs.CV, cs.HC, cs.LG, cs.IR, cs.MM

Reasoning: 
- cs.CV (Computer Vision) is the most likely category as the paper presents a new eye-tracking database for animal-centric object classes in the Pascal VOC 2012 image set, and discusses how feature pooling around fixated locations can enhance object classification accuracy.
- cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction) is also likely as the paper discusses eye movement recordings for both free-viewing and visual search task conditions, which can inform the design of interfaces and visualizations.
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is a possible category as the paper discusses how feature pooling can improve object classification accuracy, which is a common task in machine learning.
- cs.IR (Information Retrieval) is a possible category as the paper discusses how eye-tracking data can be used to improve object classification accuracy, which is relevant to information retrieval tasks such as image search.
- cs.MM (Multimedia) is a possible category as the paper discusses a new dataset for animal-centric object classes in images, which is relevant to multimedia applications such as image and video analysis.
